jason epstein  modis inc  zoominfocom jason epstein  comcast corporation  zoominfocom jason epstein  wikipedia jason epstein from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search epstein announcing the  national book critics circles ivan sandrof award for lifetime achievement epstein won the award in  jason wolkow epstein born january   is an american editor and publisher contents  life and career  awards  publications  personal life  references  external links life and careeredit born in cambridge massachusetts epstein attended public schools in milton massachusetts he graduated from columbia college of columbia university in 99 and was elected to phi beta kappa he received a master of arts degree from columbia the following year and joined doubleday and company as an editorial trainee at doubleday he saw the need for inexpensive well made paperbacks of the kinds of books that his classmates many of them veterans studying on the gi bill were reading but couldnt afford to own in their hardcover editions with the support of ken mccormick doubledays chief editor he launched anchor books the first socalled quality paperbacks which quickly became the dominant paperback format in 9 anchor books won the careythomas award in 98 he left doubleday to join random house where he served as editorial director until his retirement in 999 at random house he edited such writers as jane jacobs norman mailer philip roth derek jeter gore vidal vladimir nabokov e l doctorow michael korda and peter matthiessen during the new york newspaper strike of 9 epstein his wife barbara and their friends robert lowell and elizabeth hardwick created the new york review of books and turned to their friend robert silvers to be its editor along with epsteins wife barbara in 99 with the critic edmund wilson he conceived the library of america wellmade reliable editions of important american writers with the support of the ford foundation and the national endowment for the humanities the first volumes were published in 98 he later published the readers catalogue of 0 titles available by mail order an analog precursor of online book selling in 00 he cofounded on demand books marketer of the espresso book machine which reproduces a paperback book from a digital file in a few minutes epstein has predicted that the espresso book machine will supplant the 00yearold gutenberg technology awardsedit epstein has received the national book award for distinguished service to american letters the curtis benjamin award of the association of american publishers for creative publishing the bulldog award the lifetime achievement award of the national book critic’s circle and the philolexian award for distinguished literary achievement publicationsedit his essays and reviews have appeared in the new york times magazine the new york review of books and condé nast traveler among other publications he is the author of the following books book business publishing past present and future w w norton  company january  isbn 98090988  eating a memoir a a knopf october 9  isbn 988  east hampton a history and guide with elizabeth barlow random house may  98 isbn 9809  the great conspiracy trial random house 90 isbn 9809900  personal lifeedit in 9 jason epstein married barbara zimmerman with whom he had two children jacob and helen the couple divorced in 990 and in 99 he married judith miller a reporter for the new york times referencesedit  anchor books doubleday  book series list publishinghistorycom retrieved 0 may 0  satterfield jay the worlds best books   history and mission the library of america   lehmannhaupt christopher october  989 books of the times a catalogue as reference and revolution the new york times   epstein jason january  book business w w norton  company isbn 98090988   smith dinitia january   a vision for books that exults in happenstance the new york times   national book critics circle ivan sandrof lifetime achievement award  external linksedit wikimedia commons has media related to jason epstein jason epstein 9 looks back  and ahead alumni profile columbiaedu jacob epstein  the new york review of books  bibliography of contributed articles interview with charlie rose on ebooks and the future of publishing january   interview with charlie rose about eating a memoir january   appearances on cspan cspans booknotes interview with epstein on book business publishing past present and future march 8  authority control worldcat identities viaf 99 lccn n89 isni 0  8 80 sudoc 09 bnf cb8 data retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlejasonepsteinoldid8808 categories  birthsliving peopleamerican information and reference writersamerican male journalistsamerican publishers peoplecolumbia university alumnithe new york review of booksphi beta kappa membershidden categories wikipedia articles with viaf identifierswikipedia articles with lccn identifierswikipedia articles with isni identifierswikipedia articles with bnf identifiers navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity portalrecent changescontact page tools what links hererelated changesupload filespecial pagespermanent linkpage informationwikidata itemcite this page printexport create a bookdownload as pdfprintable version in other projects wikimedia commons languages add links this page was last edited on  june 0 at 8 text is available under the creative commons attributionsharealike license additional terms may apply by using this site you agree to the terms of use and privacy policy wikipedia® is a registered trademark of the wikimedia foundation inc a nonprofit organization privacy policy about wikipedia disclaimers contact wikipedia developers cookie statement mobile view jason epstein  wikipedia jason epstein fr