idge massachusetts epstein attended public schools in milton massachusetts he graduated from columbia college of columbia university in 99 and was elected to phi beta kappa he received a master of arts degree from columbia the following year and joined doubleday and company as an editorial trainee at doubleday he saw the need for inexpensive well made paperbacks of the kinds of books that his classmates many of them veterans studying on the gi bill were reading but couldnt afford to own in their hardcover editions with the support of ken mccormick doubledays chief editor he launched anchor books the first socalled quality paperbacks which quickly became the dominant paperback format in 9 anchor books won the careythomas award in 98 he left doubleday to join random house where he served as editorial director until his retirement in 999 at random house he edited such writers as jane jacobs norman mailer philip roth derek jeter gore vidal vladimir nabokov e l doctorow michael korda and peter matthiessen during the new york newspaper strike of 9 epstein his wife barbara and their friends robert lowell and elizabeth hardwick created the new york review of books and turned to their friend robert silvers to be its editor along with epsteins wife barbara in 99 with the critic edmund wilson he conceived the library of america wellmade reliable editions of important american writers with the support of the ford foundation and the national endowment for the humanities the first volumes were published in 98 he later published the readers catalogue of 0 titles available by mail order an analog precursor of online book selling in 00 he cofounded on demand books marketer of the espresso book machine which reproduces a paperback book from a digital file in a few minutes epstein has predicted that the espresso book machine will supplant the 00yearold gutenberg technology awardsedit epstein has received the national book award for distinguished service to american letters the curtis 